@node "About" " About SHI Support BBS Guide (Rev. 01-09-94)"
@next "SHIMAIN"
@prev "main"

This SHI Support BBS Guide, was made because there sometimes are some FAKE
viruskillers around. When you use this guide to find a BBS in your country
you can be sure, that there are NO fake viruskillers on that BBS.

SHI Team Denmark,  will not take any  responsibility for amy wrong data in
this guide. We will try to keep the BBS data, as right as possible.

This guide is freeware, this means that you can copy it freely. This guide
cannot be used for commercial purposes without written permission from the
author.

SHI Support BBS.Guide may not be modified in any way. It is not allowed to
use the  guide in other  guide files,  without written permission from the
author.

The SHI Support BBS.guide may be released in public domain disk libraries,
compilation disks,  club newsletters  or any other  kind of disk  with the
exception of commercially sold Anti-Virus disks.

Special permission is hereby granted to include the guide in Public-Domain
collections such as Fred Fish's Amiga Library.

Please help us !!!. If you find a new virus, do not delete it, upload to a
SHI Support BBS,  in the area 'UPLOAD VIRUS TO SHI'. And we will send that
virus, to all the well known anti-virus programmers.

Regards..... Jan Andersen        @{" SHI Team Denmark " link SHIDK }.
             Lars P. Kristensen  @{" SHI Team Denmark " link SHIDK }.
@endnode

@node "SHIMAIN" "SHI MAIN CENTRAL VIRUS CENTRE"
