@node "SHISUPPORT" "How to become an SHI Support BBS"
@next "RegForm"
@prev "SHIDK"

  If you want to be an SHI Support BBS, you can get our support if you can
 agree to these demands:

   1...  That your BBS  is open 24 hours,  you have a modem  with at least
        14.400 baud, and that you only have the newest updates of the best
        viruskillers. ( That means,  that you don't have VirusX, ZeroVirus
        and old killers like that ).

   2...  That you have a lot of text files made by SHI on your board, in a
        special area for them. You can get all the text files  if you call
        @{" SHI MAIN BBS " link "SHIMAIN" } or  you  can send  money to @{" SHI Team Denmark " link "SHIDK" } with
        some disks  and then  we will fill  them with text files and  send
        the  back to  you.  That's where the money you send us will go, to
        pay the return postage for the disks.

   3...  That you make a  text in  your  bulletin-menu,  with a  text that
        tells the users what  the newest  updates of the  killers are, and
        the date they  were made.  And a  little  text about  SHI in  your
        bulletin menu. Also that you mention in your  login  menu that you
        run an SHI support BBS.

   4...   And you  make one area where the users can upload new viruses to
        SHI. And you will send these new virus to SHI Main BBS, as fast as
        you can.

   5...  That you will  give other  SHI Support SysOps  free  downloads on
        your board.


  If you can agree to these demands, you wil get this:

   1...  Free  downloads from  the SHI Main BBS  and all the other support
        BBS in the world.

   2...  You will get your  name in this textfile. And you can call @{"SHI" link "SHIMAIN" } if
        you have trouble with viruses.

   3...  If you send  money and disks to SHI, then we will  put the newest
        updates of the best  killers on them,  and send them right back to
        you. The money is to pay for the return postage of the disks.

   4...  If SHI gets a call  from a user,  we will tell him to contact the
        Support BBS in his country.

   5...  You will  get your BBS name in the  logoff texts on other Support
        BBS'es, if they are using this. SHI Main BBS will  write your name
        there.


        We hope that you will join us!!

                                   Regards

                      Lars P. Kristensen & Jan Andersen.

               @{" Yes, I would like to be an SHI Support BBS " link "RegForm" }
@endnode

