@node "Maus-Iserlohn" " Maus-Iserlohn BBS - Germany"

  BBS Name...... : Maus Iserlohn-Kalthof.

  BBS Software.. : Maus Version 7.94e6.

  SysOp......... : Martin Loos.

  Modem......... : ZyXEL U-1496E.

  Phone Number.. : +49 2371 460879.

  HD Space...... : 200 MB.

  Open Hours.... : 00.00-3.40 / 6.00-20.45 / 21.30-23.59.

  Voice Phone... : +49 2371 46665.

  Fido Number... : 2:2444/4504.2.

  AmigaNet Number: None.

  UseNet-Address : postmaster@mk2.maus.sauerland.de.

  Comment:
  --------

  The Maus Iserlohn-Kalthof BBS is part of the german "MausNet" and is
  online sinse May 17, 1994. The MausNet is the fastest private network
  in Germany, Austria and Switzerland and contains about 110 BBSs).

  We are an official support BBS for UMS (The Universal Message System).
  The SysOps are programmers of UMS (together with Matthias "Filer" Scheler,
  Martin Horneffer, Stefan "Toolmanager" Becker, Kai "AMOK" Bolay,
  Stefan "MUI" Stuntz and about 20 other well known Amiga programmers).

  The Maus Iserlohn-Kalthof has Gateways to FidoNet, NetMK and UseNet.
  We have allways a big part of new releases of Amiga-Software, because
  we have access to AmiNet (The Internet-Servers from which the AmiNet-
  CD-ROMs are made).

  Guests may download any of the soft found on our BBS. There is no
  Up-/Download-ratio or download-limitation.

  The Sysops:
  Martin Loos    (mattin@mk2.maus.sauerland.de)
  Michael Gehrke (manor@mk2.maus.sauerland.de)
  Dirk Reinarz   (dr@mk2.maus.sauerland.de)
@endnode

